title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson Model 29-2
postcontent: This listing is for a beautiful one of a kind unfired Smith and Wesson 6.5" model 29-2 .44 magnum engraved by Joseph Condon aka "Engraver to the Stars" (now deceased). The entire gun was designed, engraved and inlaid with solid gold by Condon in 1981 (see signature and date in trigger guard). Grips are scrimshaw engraved solid IVORY. The engraving commemorates the Clint Eastwood movies "Dirty Harry" "Magnum Force" and "The Enforcer". Condon considered this piece to be his lifetime masterpiece. The pistol shows a gold figure of Dirty Harry with his Model 29 in high relief 3D gold which literally comes out of the revolver frame. There is also a man-sized target in the background. There is a gold figure of Alcatraz, the Warner Brothers logo and the Golden Gate Bridge. Included with the gun is a plaque describing the design which was made by Condon with the gun (see photos). The gun is in perfect condition. There is a piece missing from the right side grip. It was a gold star representing the inspector's badge. The badge was missing when I purchased the gun.

I will install drop-in trigger kits, like an Apex kit, for $25.  I will do repairs and parts replacements or enhancements on any modern semi-automatic pistol from manufacturers such as Beretta, Colt, FN, HK, Glock, Kahr, Kimber, Ruger, Sig Sauer, Smith & Wesson, Springfield Armory and all makes of 1911s. If you buy a gun and parts for that gun such as an extended slide lock lever or extended magazine release, I will install the parts for free.

My turnaround times are measured in minutes, hours or days versus weeks or even months for some shops.
